# AGENTS.md — {{.AppName}}

## Context

This is the {{.AppName}} application of {{.ProjectName}}.

{{if eq .AppType "backend"}}
## Backend-Specific Rules

- HTTP handlers must not contain business logic.
- Domain layer must not import infrastructure packages.
- Errors must be typed and wrapped with context.
- Every new endpoint needs contract tests.
- Database migrations must be backward-compatible.
- Use dependency injection for all external services.
{{end}}

{{if eq .AppType "frontend"}}
## Frontend-Specific Rules

- Every component must be in its own file.
- Use {{.Stack.Frontend.Framework}} functional components with hooks.
- Style with {{.Stack.Frontend.Styling}}.
- No inline styles — use class-based styling.
- Every page must be responsive.
- Test all user interactions.
{{end}}

## Commands

{{if eq .AppType "backend"}}
{{if eq .Stack.Backend.Language "go"}}
```bash
cd apps/api
go test ./...
go vet ./...
go build -o bin/api ./cmd/api
```
{{else if eq .Stack.Backend.Framework "nestjs"}}
```bash
cd apps/api
npm install
npm run start:dev
npm test
npm run build
```
{{end}}
{{end}}

{{if eq .AppType "frontend"}}
```bash
cd apps/web
npm install
npm run dev
npm test
npm run build
```
{{end}}

